    ['Chameleon Capers'] = {
        id = 84,
        start_npc = 'Luto Mewrilah',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-8',
        description = 'A friend of Luto has used a magical costume kit to change into a child, but now he can\'t return to his original form. Luto wants you to help find a way to change him back.',
        reward = 'One of three Tactics Manuals',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Luto for a cutscene to begin the quest.\n2. Go to Ru\'Lude Gardens (H-7) and speak to Muhoho on the balcony of the Grand Ducal Palace.\n3. Go to Bastok Mines (H-7) and speak to Gelzerio in Boytz\'s Knicknacks.\n4. Go to Windurst Waters north map (F-10) and speak to Chamama in the Rarab Tail Hostelry to receive [Key Item] Jar of reversion dust.\n5. Return to Upper Jeuno and speak to Luto, then go to Lower Delkfutt\'s Tower.\n   - Ensure that you have your Signal Pearl in your inventory/Wardrobe/Satchel/Sack. You may receive another from speaking with your Fellow.\n   - First go to (J-9) and examine the ??? spot, then to (I-5) to examine another ??? spot.  Go to (J-9) and examine the ??? spot in the pool to pop a NM named Illusory Pot and your Adventuring Fellow.\n6. Once you defeat the magic pot, speak to your Adventuring Fellow, then examine the ??? spot for a final cutscene that ends the quest.  Where you will be able to chose one of the following three items.\nTo teach a new job to your Adventuring Fellow, simply visit any city Rendezvous Point with the manual in your inventory.  Tactics Manuals are not consumed, and are not exclusive allowing you to trade or buy them from Bazaars to learn all three extra jobs.\nYou can buy the remaining manuals from Ajahkeem for Fellow Points.\nIf you select the correct option during the cutscene (left), you get an additional dialog at the end, but it doesn\'t seem to affect anything else:\n7. Fellow: I was impressed you were able to tell which was the real me, .\n8. Luto: Maybe when people trust each other fully, you can see rrright past their exterior and into their soul.\n9. Luto: It seems you two are bound together even more deeply than I suspected.',
