        description = 'A chocobo has run away from the stables in Upper Jeuno, and Brutus wants you to help bring it back.',
        reward = 'Chocobo Egg',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Head to Upper Jeuno and speak to Brutus at (G-7).\n   - Help the chocobo leave when prompted.\n2. Head to La Theine Plateau and check the Chocobo Tracks at the far northwest corner of (E-5), just south of the sliver of map in (E-4).\n3. Return to Upper Jeuno and speak to Brutus (G-7) again.\n4. Head to Southern San d\'Oria and speak to Hantileon (I-11).\n   - You are given three choices to select.\n   - All choices are incorrect, but you must choose them anyway.\n     - Select "Bring the chocobos together"\n5. Return to Brutus (G-7) in Upper Jeuno one last time to complete the quest.\n6. Speak to Brutus (G-7) after one game day to receive a chocobo egg.\n     - You must change zones and return to Upper Jeuno after the day change. Logging off and logging back on after the day changing without zoning will not trigger this cutscene, also.\nOptional:\nTrade the egg to one of the VCS Trainers located in Bastok Mines, Southern San d\'Oria, or Windurst Woods to begin raising a chocobo.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Chocobo\'s Wounds'] = {
        id = 4,
        start_npc = 'Brutus',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-7',
        description = 'Help nurse the chocobo back to health. It seems to have suffered both mentally and physically. Gausebit wildgrass may do the trick.',
        reward = '[Key Item] Chocobo license',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'Chocobo Trainer',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = {
            'Save My Son',
            'Full Speed Ahead!',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Gausebit Grass', count = 4},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. To begin, speak to Brutus at (G-7) on any job level 20 or higher, this starts the quest Chocobo on the Loose!.\n2. Speak to him two more times to start the correct quest, and choose "Nope, never!".\n3. Obtain Gausebit Grass x4.\n   - They can be purchased from the Auction House under Weapons > Ammo & Misc. > Pet Items\n   - Can be farmed in Meriphataud Mountains from Crane Flies, or in Dangruf Wadi from Wadi Hares.\n     - The crane flies are on the northern part of the map - by the outpost (and survival guide) or around the entrance to Castle Oztroja.\n     - There isn\'t a super close Unity Warp to these locations for initial transit if you have yet to get a nearby Survival Guide:\n     - The best bet might be the 122 Meriphataud Mountains, though it is near to the zone line with Tahrongi Canyon.\n     - :The 125 Sauromugue Champaign is also significantly more northward than would be ideal.\n     - For Dangruf Wadi, the 75 South Gustaberg warp is closest if you don\'t have the Dangruf Wadi survival guide.\n   - Do not confuse this with Gysahl Greens which are sold from the stables NPC. They do not work.\n4. Feed the chocobo standing next to Osker one Gausebit Grass by trading it to the chocobo.\n   - It is possible to feed the chocobo once every real life minute.\n     - Each "minute" starts at :00  (rather than counting from the last feeding interaction with the chocobo)\n   - It will take 6 feeding attempts to complete the quest.\n     - The first 2 attempts will automatically fail, and will not consume a grass.\n   - You can use a macro or chat command to speed up the process: /item \'gausebit grass\'\n     - Tip: Stand closer to the Chocobo than to Osker and use F8 (or the target-closest-NPC button) to re-target the chocobo between attempts, as interaction will cause your target to be de-selected even if it\'s locked. If you\'re using the chat directly, press / and then the up arrow to repeat the last command you typed.\n5. Once the chocobo eats the Gausebit Grass x4, you are presented with a [Key Item] Chocobo license.\n:\n6. You don\'t need to zone before starting the next quest, Full Speed Ahead!\n   - ...but you\'ll need the Map of the Jeuno area (available from Rusese inside M&P Market at H-6 for 600 gil) before Mapitoto will acknowledge you.',
        notes = nil,
    },
