        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-7',
        description = 'Laila has asked that you bring her a stardust pebble before she\'ll consider allowing you to join Troupe Brilioth.',
        reward = 'Ability to become a Dancer',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'Troupe Brilioth Dancer',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = nil,
        next = {'The Unfinished Waltz'},
        requirements = {
            {name = '[Key Item] Stardust pebble', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak with Laila in Upper Jeuno to begin the quest.\n   - You must choose "I surely do." and then "Never!" to continue.\n2. She will then ask for a [Key Item] Stardust pebble.\n3. Speak with the mithran dancer, Rhea Myuliah, next to her.\n   - If you speak to Laila and Rhea Myuliah answers, continue on to the next step.\n4. Head to Lion Springs Tavern at (K-6) in Southern San d\'Oria and speak to Valderotaux at the bar to \'dance\'" select the last option.\n5. Return to Rhea Myuliah in Upper Jeuno to discover what the pebbles are.\n6. Travel to the past and go to (I-5) in Jugner Forest (S).\n   - Coming from Batallia Downs (S) Survival Guide is the fastest way to get to (I-5) in Jugner Forest (S).\n7. Touch the glowing pebbles targetable location for a cutscene, and then return to Laila afterwards to finish unlocking the Dancer job.\n   - Note: This spot is not actually glowing, unlike other targetable locations in the game. It is simply a targetable spot in the environment. Target around at (I-5) and pay attention to your target names in order to find the spot.\n8. Speak with Laila in Upper Jeuno once more to finish the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
