        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Luto for a cutscene that begins the quest.  She will ask you to check on your Adventuring Fellow who is in the Infirmary.\n2. Speak to Monberaux at (G-10) for a cutscene, then return to Luto for another cutscene.\n3. Head to Qufim Island and go to (E-6) to find a Giant Footprint.\n   - You need to head north past Delkfutt tower and follow the tunnel to (E-6).  It is next to a cermet spine.\n4. Examining it will pop a Gigas NM Ingaevon and your Adventuring Fellow.  Defeat Ingaevon, then speak to your Adventuring Fellow.\n   - The gigas can be spawned again 3 minutes after it\'s killed.\n5. Return to Luto in Upper Jeuno for a cutscene, then speak to Monberaux for a cutscene that completes the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Researchers from the West'] = {
        id = 171,
        start_npc = 'Anastase',
        start_zone = 'Ru\'Lude Gardens',
        start_pos = 'G-9',
        description = 'A research expedition from the Sacred City of Adoulin is seeking collaborators. They require information about geomagnetic founts in various areas to assist in the testing of their mystical devices.',
        reward = 'Proto-Waypoint Teleportation\n3 Trail Cookie\n400 Conquest points',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = {
            'Middle Lands Investigation',
            'Granddaddy Dearest',
        },
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Anastase in Ru\'Lude Gardens and choose to partake in his quest to receive the Prototype attuner.\n2. At this point, you must discover four additional Proto-Waypoints hidden throughout Vana\'diel by using the hints provided upon asking Anastase about his prognostications.\n3. After discovering each Proto-Waypoints, speak to the NPC standing nearby to activate teleportation:\n   - : Pure white beaches... Clay... Disembowelment...\n     - Selbina (G-10) - Talk to Jillia.\n   - : A long-necked beast... A chef in search of meat from the beast... "The Old Lady"...\n     - Mhaura (I-8) -  Talk to Zurko-Bazurko.\n   - : A windmill... A large lake... An island where sand stretches to the sky...\n     - Rabao (G-8) -  Talk to Quwi Orihbhe.\n   - : Samurai and ninjas... Pirates... Contraband...\n     - Norg (G-7) -  Talk to Wistful Bison.\n4. Once you have spoken to all four NPCs, return to Anastase.\n   - It is worth noting that simply flagging the first quest gives you the opportunity to flag any of the subsequent teleports and use them without completing the quests. So, for instance, once you\'ve flagged Researches from the West you can unlock any of the geomagnetic founts associated with the subsequent quests like Quicksand caves and warp to them.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Riding on the Clouds'] = {
        id = 131,
        start_npc = 'Maat',
        start_zone = 'Ru\'Lude Gardens',
        start_pos = 'H-5',
        description = 'Use Maat\'s hints to search out four people who will trade you a strange stone for a Kindred\'s seal. Only then will you know your true limits.',
        reward = 'Raises level cap to 70.',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'Cloud Breaker',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Whence Blows the Wind'},
        next = {'Shattering Stars'},
        requirements = {
            {name = 'x4 Kindred\'s Seals', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Maat on a level 61+ job. He will give you four clues and wishes for you to trade a Kindred\'s Seal to the people described in the clues. You are not provided with the Kindred\'s Seals and will need to procure them in order to complete this quest.\n2. Check your storage Satchel, Sack, or Case (the command /itemsearch "Kindred\'s seal" can help), and/or with Port Jeuno NPCs Shemo and Shami (Menu –> Status –> Currencies –> Kindred\'s Seals Stored), as you may already have enough seals. Not to be confused with Kindred\'s Crest which drops on level 70+ mobs.\n3. A reminder that Kindred\'s seals can be acquired from:\n   - Any normal mob level 50-69 that checks as Easy Prey or higher.\n   - Exchanged 3:1 (or 2:1 during certain campaigns) for other seal types from Shemo.\n   - The Greeter Moogles for 10 points each, if redemption for a login points campaign is currently active.\n     - Note that you\'ll need 5 seals more for New Worlds Await, so you may wish to acquire them at the same time – which together would be 9 total for 90 points.\n4. In return for a Seal, you will receive either a [Key Item] Smiling stone, [Key Item] Scowling stone, [Key Item] Somber stone, or [Key Item] Spirited stone.\n   - Three clues will refer to someone in one person each in San d\'Oria, Bastok, and Windurst.\n   - The final clue will refer to someone in either Selbina or Mhaura.\n   - The above are in no particular order, but all four locations are guaranteed.\n5. Speak to Maat once you have all four stones to complete the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
