    ['The Flying Machine of Eld'] = {
        id = 186,
        start_npc = 'Jeridade',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Jeridade has a dream: to create a flying machine for the ages. If you have any leads, be sure to bring them to Mapitoto.',
        reward = 'Levitus key',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Full Speed Ahead!'},
        next = nil,
        requirements = {
            {name = ': Green Chip\n: Infinity Core\n: Ve\'Lugannon Coffer Key\n: Elemental Crystal Cluster x38', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Approach the chocobo stable in Upper Jeuno (G-7).\n      - You may have to zone after completing the previous quest.\n2. Complete the The Celestial Nexus II, on any difficulty, to get the Broken flying machine Key Item.\n3. Report back to Mapitoto.\n4. Visit the Strange Apparatus in Fei\'Yin (G-6 map 1) for your next clue.\n      - You will need to proceed to the basement (H-9, Map 1) or warp to the Fauregandi → Fei\'Yin → Home Point #2.\n         - Then proceed back upstairs from (E-7, Map 2) to (G/H-6, Map 1) to run through the fake wall and to the Apparatus. All apparatuses are hidden like this.\n5. Obtain a  Ve\'Lugannon Coffer Key and open a coffer in Ve\'Lugannon Palace to obtain the Levitation device Key Item.\n      - Curio Vendor Moogles sell the Coffer Key for 5,000 gil.\n      - If you are in a party, all members will receive the Key Item when one member opens a coffer.\n         - Notice: If someone who\'s in your party but doesn\'t need the Key Item opens the coffer, no one will get the Key Item.\n         - Advice: You can make a full party, leave 1 person at each blue/yellow gate control and send others to find the coffer, so long as someone who needs the Key Item opens the coffer everyone in the same party (not alliance) will get it. Just make sure to keep everyone who needs it in the same zone as the coffer or it won\'t count for them.\n6. Obtain Doctor Status from any Strange Apparatus and return to the one in Fei\'Yin and examine the Apparatus.\n      - You will not be able to obtain Doctor Status from the apparatus in Fei\'Yin.\n         - Once obtained, the status will persist after obtaining it in another zone and returning.\n         - Warning: Don\'t accidentally trade your items to a Strange Apparatus in another zone than the one in Fei\'Yin for this quest! The Strange Apparatus of another zone will overload with the items from this quest an summon a strong elemental to fight you. You will also lose your Green Chip but if you slay the elemental it has a chance at another Infinity Core.\n      - Optional: If you want to save time for the Omega whistle go visit Boisterous Jackal in Lower Jeuno (H-7) and speak with him 2 times to enable the circumstances for  Administrator Status in Fei\'Yin since your going there next anyway you can save a trip. Also this status doesn\'t seem to expire unlike the \'Doctor Status\'.\n7. Trade the  Green Chip and  Infinity Core to the apparatus in Fei\'Yin.\n      - The apparatus will then ask for 38  elemental crystal clusters. Any combination of elements works.\n         - Bringing these ahead of time helps as you won\'t find out until after trading the chip and core.\n8. Trade the stacks of crystal clusters to obtain the Whirring engine Key Item.\n9. Return to Mapitoto to get the Levitus key Key Item.\n   - Note: The Levitus inventory item exists in the game, but you are given the Key Item directly.',
        notes = nil,
    },
