    ['The Goblin Tailor'] = {
        id = 42,
        start_npc = 'Guttrix',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'H-10',
        description = 'Each week, a different magical pattern appears inside a treasure chest somewhere. Give it to Guttrix and he\'ll reward you.',
        reward = 'Varies',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '3',
        title = 'Goblin\'s Exclusive Fashion Mannequin',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Ordelle Chest Key, or Gusgen Chest Key, or Shakhrami Chest Key', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Guttrix, who will offer to make you Race Specific Equipment (RSE) if you bring him a [Key Item] Magical pattern.\n   - [Key Item] Magical patterns are found in Treasure Chests in Gusgen Mines, Ordelle\'s Caves, and Maze of Shakhrami.\n   - You need to find the chests at the right time. Treasure maps for the zones are below (blue squares are chest spawns).\n   - Alternately, adventurers in possession of the [Key Item] "Rhapsody in White" can purchase these keys for 2,500g from a Curio Vendor Moogle.\n2. Each race is given a game week (Firesday to Darksday) to find a pattern. At the end of that game week, it will become the next race\'s turn.\n   - The race order is Hume Male -> Hume Female -> Elvaan Male -> Elvaan Female -> Tarutaru Male -> Tarutaru Female -> Mithra -> Galka.\n   - Each game week is 7 hours 40 minutes 48 seconds, meaning about every 8 hours the pattern changes.\n   - The following sites provide RSE calendar details:\n     - https://www.mithrapride.org/vana_time/\n     - https://www.pyogenes.com/ffxi/timer/v2.html\n   - You must open the treasure chest when it is your race\'s week or you will not get the pattern.\n   - You may only have one pattern on you at a time. However, there is no limit to the number of patterns you may re-obtain (as long as it is within your RSE week).\n3. Turn the pattern into Guttrix, who will give you the option to craft it into one of the following four (4) armors:\n4.  (Body)\n5.  (Hands)\n6.  (Legs)\n7.  (Feet)\n8.  (Body)\n9.  (Hands)\n10.  (Legs)\n11.  (Feet)\n12.  (Body)\n13.  (Hands)\n14.  (Legs)\n15.  (Feet)\n16.  (Body)\n17.  (Hands)\n18.  (Legs)\n19.  (Feet)\n20.  (Body)\n21.  (Hands)\n22.  (Legs)\n23.  (Feet)\n24.  (Body)\n25.  (Hands)\n26.  (Legs)\n27.  (Feet)\n28.  (Body)\n29.  (Hands)\n30.  (Legs)\n31.  (Feet)\n32. The hand and feet pieces can be upgraded via the event Strange Happenings in Vana\'diel.',
        notes = nil,
    },
