        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Mertaire at Merry Minstrel in Lower Jeuno (I-8).\n2. Speak to Bki Tbujhja at the counter in the same room in Lower Jeuno (H-8).\n3. Obtain a Parchment from the Auction House (Leathercraft) or by crafting.\n   - Parchment can also be bought from Pikini-Mikini in the warehouse in Mhaura (G-9) for just over 2,000 gil.\n4. Travel to Buburimu Peninsula at (G-9) and examine the Song Runes for a cutscene.\n   - To arrive at the location: go to the beach just west of Mhaura via the ramp at (H-9). Head to the southwest corner and into the water. There will be a tunnel which leads to the next beach area over, where you will find the Song Runes.\n5. Trade a Parchment to the Song Runes in Buburimu Peninsula at (G-9) for a Poetic Parchment and to complete the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Requiem'] = {
        id = 64,
        start_npc = 'Bki Tbujhja',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'H-8',
        description = 'A certain post is rotated at the meadhouse. Now, it\'s your turn.',
        reward = 'Choral Slippers \n[Key Item] Star ring (tarnished)',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'Yes',
        previous = {'Painful Memory'},
        next = {
            'The Circle of Time',
            'Borghertz\'s Harmonious Hands',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Holy Water', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Bki Tbujhja to begin the quest; she will request a flask of holy water.\n2. Trade Bki Tbujhja the Holy Water and you will be asked to travel to The Eldieme Necropolis and to visit the tomb of a a great bard of yesteryear. Once there you are to purify the tomb and play the requiem. She returns the flask of holy water and sends you on your way.\n   - (Optional) Speak to Malatigeat at the meadhouse for more information on this \'great bard of yesteryear\'.\nFrom this point on, the quest can be completed on any job.\n3. Travel to The Eldieme Necropolis via (F-5) in Batallia Downs and head for a room with five unbroken sarcophagi at D-4.\n   - You will have to travel through Beaucedine Glacier to reach the barrow containing the proper entrance to the Necropolis complex.\n   - If you have unlocked the Lycopodium (NPC) teleport service for Batallia Downs, trading one of the accepted flowers to the sparkling light (blank target) at (F-5) teleports the player to the elevated portion of the map.\n   - The quickest way is to take the Voidwatch warp to Beaucedine Glacier.\n     - Beaucedine Glacier - Unity Warp will take you near it.\n4. Trade the flask of Holy Water to the sarcophagus to spawn three skeleton NMs. The sarcophagus that will spawn the NMs is random.\n   - Side with three, one closest to the exit door\n5. Defeat all three NMs that spawn, then interact with the same sarcophagus again. You will get a cutscene and receive the [Key Item] Star ring (tarnished).\n   - If you have multiple people doing this quest, they can trade their holy water to the correct sarcophagus after the fight and they will get the cutscene and ring.\n6. Return to Bki Tbujhja and receive your Choral Slippers.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Road to Aht Urhgan'] = {
        id = 91,
        start_npc = 'Faursel',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'J-8',
        description = 'If you want to ride the mercenary transport ship from Mhaura, you must bring the required items to the Tenshodo.',
        reward = '[Key Item] Boarding permit\nMap of Wajaom Woodlands (Only if you take the 500,000 Gil route)',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Tenshodo Membership', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Faursel  (Neptune\'s Spire J-8) for a cutscene.\n2. He will give you three options to choose from. The third is a hidden option on the bottom. Choose the hidden option.\n3. Talk to Faursel a second time for another cutscene and choose "I want to go".\n4. Faursel will give you four ways to proceed: the Advanced path, the Intermediate path, the Beginner path, or paying 500,000 Gil.\n5. Collect the required item(s) for Faursel. See the options below for your options.\n   - Tip! You can buy Coffer Keys from the Curio Moogle for 5,000 Gil if you have the [Key Item] "Rhapsody in Umber". If you have not progressed in Rhapsodies of Vana\'diel, now it is by far the easiest choice even though it is "Advanced".\n6. Trade the requested item(s) to him. He will tell you to return tomorrow.\n7. Zone and return to Lower Jeuno the next game day. Talk to Faursel again to obtain the [Key Item] Boarding permit.\n   - If you wish to skip obtaining the request items, you can pay him 500,000 Gil.\n     - If you choose to pay the gil, you must change zones and return to Lower Jeuno the next game day. Then talk to Faursel and you will receive the [Key Item] Boarding permit and Map of Wajaom Woodlands and be teleported to the Leypoint in Wajaom Woodlands.\n   - If you chose not to pay the gil, you are instructed to go to Mhaura and ride the Near East from the port to Al Zahbi.\n     - If you have joined a Unity and have (or get) 100 Unity Accolades, you may skip the boat ride by using a Unity Warp with any Unity NPC -- But you must first obtain the [Key Item] Boarding permit to unlock the Aht Urghan warp options.\n     - 125 Wajaom Woodlands option, and then chocobo/run to Al Zhabi, and then through there to Aht Urghan Whitegate.\n8. After completing this quest approach Naja Salaheem at Aht Urhgan Whitegate (I-10) to begin Aht Urhgan Mission 1: Land of Sacred Serpents.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Road to Divadom'] = {
        id = 97,
        start_npc = 'Laila',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-7',
        description = 'As a child, Laila had an inspirational encounter with a piper at Lake Mechieume in Jugner Forest. In order to become a great dancer like Laila, you should seek a skilled musician to play a tune for you.',
        reward = 'Dancer\'s Tights',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'Stardust Dancer',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'The Unfinished Waltz'},
        next = {
            'Comeback Queen',
            'Matthias',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Block of Yagudo Glue', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Laila in Upper Jeuno (G-7).\n   - To complete this quest, you must have a Block of Yagudo Glue. It would save time to obtain it before the next step.\n     - Obtained from Yagudo Piper, Yagudo Lutenist, Yagudo Chanter, Yagudo Conductor, or Yagudo Drummer in a Shadowreign zone.\n     - See the Yagudo Glue page for details on which zones these mobs are located in.\n     - If you have the Survival Guide, the easiest way to obtain this is by taking it to Meriphataud Mountains (S) and farming inside Castle Oztroja (S).\n2. Zone into Jugner Forest (S) for a cutscene.\n   - The fastest way to do this is to warp to the Survival Guide in Batallia Downs (S) if you have it.\n3. Examine the Glowing Pebbles in Jugner Forest (S) (I-5) for a cutscene.\n4. Trade the Yagudo Glue Yagudo Glue to the Glowing Pebbles in Jugner Forest (S) (I-5).\n   - You must be on Dancer to obtain this cutscene.\n5. Speak to Laila in Upper Jeuno (G-7) for a cutscene and your reward.\n   - You must be on Dancer to obtain this cutscene.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Unfinished Waltz'] = {
        id = 96,
        start_npc = 'Laila',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-7',
        description = 'Troupe Brilioth is aiming for a dance style that will captivate and enchant. Work out how to take your dancing to the next level, then come back and show Laila.',
        reward = 'War Hoop',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'Promising Dancer',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'Lakeside Minuet'},
        next = {'The Road to Divadom'},
        requirements = {
            {name = '[Key Item] The Essence of Dance', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Laila in Upper Jeuno (G-7).\n   - You must be on your Dancer job to initiate this cutscene.\n   - If you receive a cutscene where she asks about seeing you dance, your quest is now active.\n2. Speak to Rhea Myuliah next to Laila in Upper Jeuno (G-7).\n3. Head to Grauberg (S) and examine the ??? in Witchfire Glen at (F-5) for a cutscene. (The ??? in the middle of the set of three closely-packed trees very slightly NW of the Veridical Conflux.)\n   - You must be on your Dancer job to initiate this cutscene.\n   - Fastest method of travel is to use the lightsworm at any maw outside of Jeuno to enter Walk of Echoes, then exit with the conflux\n4. Examine the ??? again to spawn the NM Migratory Hippogryph.\n   - If you zone after examining it the first time, you must examine it again as a Dancer, therefore you must be on Dancer for the duration of this fight.\n5. Examine the ??? after defeating the NM for a cutscene to receive the [Key Item] The Essence of Dance.\n6. "Open" the Key Item: The Essence of Dance.\n   - Can be easily located under the Permanent Key Items menu, just after any Gate Crystal Key Items you may possess.\n7. Speak to Laila in Upper Jeuno (G-7) for a cutscene and your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Wonder Magic Set'] = {
        id = 7,
        start_npc = 'Panta-Putta',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-10',
        description = 'You are to bring Panta the popular Wonder Magic Set. Don\'t say a word to his family, or else.',
        reward = 'Mythril Earring',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '4',
        title = 'Fool\'s Errand Runner',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = {'Cook\'s Pride'},
        requirements = {
            {name = '[Key Item]Wonder Magic Set', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Naruru, Teigero-Bangero, or Panta-Putta located in the merchant\'s house in Lower Jeuno (G-10), for a cutscene.\n   - There is no Fame requirement to receive the cutscene\n2. Talk to Panta-Putta. He wants you to bring him a [Key Item]Wonder Magic Set.\n   - The [Key Item]Wonder Magic Set is obtained from the related quest Child\'s Play.\n3. Return to Panta-Putta to complete the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['To Kill Mocking Birds'] = {
        id = 178,
        start_npc = 'Nantoto',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'For adventurers of incredible aptitude whose feats in Records of Eminence are household topics of discussion: make some Yagudo High Priests in Castle Oztroja pray to their maker!',
        reward = '500 Sparks / 2500 Experience Points / Copper A.M.A.N. Voucher x12',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Observer of Fateful Cubes',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'Petals of Recollection'},
        next = {
            'Golden Rule',
            'Impermanence',
            'Panta Rhei',
            'Leonine Excruciation',
            'Shiver Me Timbers',
            'Go With the Flow',
            'Over Ninety-Thousand',
            'Minnow Wrangler',
            'A Thousand Cuts',
            'Disappointment Valley',
            'Remembrance of Flowers Past',
        },
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Nantoto at H-8 in Lower Jeuno.\n2. Activate the Records of Eminence quest under Other -> RoE Quests -> Grudge to get credit.\n3. Defeat one Yagudo High Priest in Castle Oztroja.\n   - The priest is through the trap door at the top of the castle.\n   - Refer to the Brass Statue page for passwords that allow access to the Yagudo High Priest\'s area.\n   - The sparks and EXP are awarded at this point. This objective can be completed as a monipulator if you wish to obtain the EXP for a monster rather than a job.\n4. Return to Nantoto for a cutscene and your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Unlisted Qualities'] = {
        id = 77,
        start_npc = 'Luto Mewrilah',
        start_zone = 'Upper Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'G-8',
        description = 'Luto wants you to find out if the person you chose from her list is holding a certain mirror.',
        reward = 'Silver Ingot',
        fame = 'Jeuno',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = nil,
        next = {'Girl in the Looking Glass'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Luto Mewrilah to begin the quest.  You will be given a list of the 8 races/sexes to chose from, then 8 names for each.  Select one to continue.\n2. Feliz\n3. Ferdinand\n4. Gunnar\n5. Massimo\n6. Oldrich\n7. Siegward\n8. Theobald\n9. Zenji\n10. Amerita\n11. Beatrice\n12. Henrietta\n13. Jesimae\n14. Karyn\n15. Nanako\n16. Sharlene\n17. Sieghilde\n18. Chanandit\n19. Deulmaeux\n20. Demresinaux\n21. Ephealgaux\n22. Gauldeval\n23. Grauffemart\n24. Migaifongut\n25. Romidiant\n26. Armittie\n27. Cadepure\n28. Clearite\n29. Epilleve\n30. Liabelle\n31. Nauthima\n32. Radille\n33. Vimechue\n34. Balu-Falu\n35. Burg-Ladarg\n36. Ehgo-Ryuhgo\n37. Kolui-Pelui\n38. Nokum-Akkum\n39. Savul-Kivul\n40. Vinja-Kanja\n41. Yarga-Umiga\n42. Cupapa\n43. Jajuju\n44. Kalokoko\n45. Mahoyaya\n46. Pakurara\n47. Ripokeke\n48. Yawawa\n49. Yufafa\n50. Fhig Lahrv\n51. Khuma Tagyawhan\n52. Pimy Kettihl\n53. Raka Maimhov\n54. Sahyu Banjyao\n55. Sufhi Uchnouma\n56. Tsuim Nhomango\n57. Yoli Kohlpaka\n58. Durib\n59. Dzapiwa\n60. Jugowa\n61. Mugido\n62. Voldai\n63. Wagwei\n64. Zayag\n65. Zoldof\n66. Once you have selected a race and name, Luto Mewrilah will ask you to find out information about your fellow.\n67. Speak to Akta - Ru\'Lude Gardens (H-10) to choose your fellow\'s height: short, medium, or tall.\n68. Speak to Kuah Dakonsa - Lower Jeuno (H-8) who will ask you to choose your fellow\'s face and hair.\n   - When you choose the number, you\'ll be shown a preview before confirming your choice.\n69. Speak to Red Ghost - Port Jeuno (G-8) who will ask you about your fellow\'s personality.\n   - Personality determines their dialog and which Homemade Food item they make.\n     - Each of these is an AoE Food with the same amount of Attack and Accuracy, with 1 additional stat. 30 min duration.\n70. Go to Upper Jeuno and speak to Bheem (F-5) for a cutscene.\n71. Return to Luto Mewrilah to complete the quest.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Unlocking a Myth (Bard)'] = {
        id = 111,
        start_npc = 'Zalsuhm',
        start_zone = 'Lower Jeuno',
        start_pos = 'H-9',
        description = 'Self-styled leading researcher of mystical artifacts, Zalsuhm, claims that the weapon you acquired deep within Nyzul Isle conceals immense power. Wielding the now unlocked weapon will cause a magical evolution to take place...eventually.',
        reward = 'The ability to use your job\'s Mythic Weapon Skill with any weapon of the same type.',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Vigil Weapon equipped.', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Zalsuhm (inside Muckvix\'s Junk Shop, Lower Jeuno H-9) with a Vigil Weapon equipped for a cutscene.\n2. With the same Vigil weapon equipped in the main hand, fight enemies that grant experience points (Incredibly Easy Prey or better) and perform Weapon Skills and Skillchains.\n   - Weapon skills used before starting this quest do not count.\n   - You must accumulate 250 Weapon Skill Points via the following methods:\n3. Once you have acquired enough Weapon Skill Points, your new Weapon Skill will appear under your list of Weapon Skills, but only with your Vigil Weapon still equipped.\n4. Return to Zalsuhm and trade him your Vigil Weapon.\n   - He will unlock your new Weapon Skill for use with any weapon and return the Vigil Weapon to you.',
        notes = '1. If you trade your Vigil Weapon to Zalsuhm before it is unlocked, he will give you a rough gauge on how far along you have progressed:\n   - "I sense only a mote of energy present. You still have a long way to go."\n   - "I can feel a marked increase in energy compared to when I first held it. Keep up the good work."\n   - "The energy is threatening to burst forth. It won\'t be long now."\n   - "You\'ve done it! Energy is overflowing as though the floodgates have burst open!"\n2. Storing a Vigil Weapon with Ghanraam at Aht Urhgan Whitegate (K-10) resets its Weapon Skill Points.\n3. After this quest, the Vigil Weapon can still be used for the Mythic Weapon acquisition quests.\n   - The Weapon Skill points will not be needed again, so it is okay to store it.\n4. For the first year and a half of implementation from 2007-2008, the Vigil Weapons were only obtainable on Floor 100.\n5. Prior to the July 2014 Version Update, the number of Weapon Skill Points required was determined by the number of floors the player cleared in Nyzul Isle Investigation.\n   - At some point (likely the May 2025 Version Update that also updated other :Category:WSNM quests), the point rewards per WS were significantly increased. This quest is now much faster than it used to be.',
    },
